Your Honor, 

I, Chloe Mills, stand before this court today to plead guilty to the charge of affray. I accept full responsibility for my actions and acknowledge that my behavior was inappropriate and unacceptable.

On the night in question, I was overwhelmed with emotions upon discovering that my boyfriend had cheated on me. In my anger and hurt, I made the regrettable decision to confront him at the bar where he was with his friends. While I did threaten him by mentioning a gun, it is important to note that I do not own a firearm nor possess any means of obtaining one.

During the confrontation, I did slap him in the face, but I did not cause any further harm. I acknowledge the fear and discomfort my actions may have caused to those present in the bar, and I deeply regret any distress I may have caused them. I should have handled the situation in a more composed and rational manner.

Your Honor, it is important to consider that I am a 24-year-old individual with no prior criminal record. I have consistently sought self-improvement through therapy, attending regular sessions once a week. This demonstrates my commitment to addressing the issues that led to this unfortunate incident, and my dedication to preventing any similar occurrences in the future.

I stand before you, pleading guilty, fully aware of the gravity of my actions. I express my sincere remorse for the fear and unease that I caused within the bar. I assure this court and the affected individuals that I will continue to take responsibility for my actions and work towards becoming a better person.

Thank you for allowing me the opportunity to address the court, and I hope that my genuine remorse and commitment to self-improvement will be taken into consideration when determining a just and fair sentence.
