Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, admit to the offense of affray, fully aware of the seriousness of my actions and accepting full responsibility for them.

Upon learning of my boyfriend's infidelity, I made the regrettable decision to confront him at the bar where he was in the company of his friends. In a moment of anger and frustration, I threatened to retrieve a gun, despite lacking the means to do so. It was an impulsive reaction, fueled by my emotions and the desire to uncover the truth.

While I did slap my boyfriend during our altercation, it was the extent of the physical harm caused. I acknowledge that my behavior may have caused distress to other patrons, and I sincerely apologize for any fear or discomfort I may have caused them. Looking back on the situation, I fully realize that there were alternative, more composed ways to handle my emotions, and I deeply regret not choosing one of those paths.

I humbly request that the court takes into consideration the circumstances surrounding this incident. Prior to this offense, my character has been devoid of any criminal activity. Furthermore, I am actively engaged in therapy, attending sessions once a week, as part of my commitment to personal growth and self-improvement. Therapy has proven instrumental in helping me develop healthier coping mechanisms and emotional management skills.

I express genuine remorse for my actions and pledge to learn from this experience. I earnestly hope that my demonstrations of remorse, along with my commitment to self-improvement, will be factored into any sentencing decision. I understand the consequences of my actions and am prepared to accept any appropriate punishment.

Thank you for granting me the opportunity to address the court.
